# HTML and CSS Standards

## Layout Structure
- Base layout: [_layouts/default.html](mdc:_layouts/default.html)
- Post layout: [_layouts/post.html](mdc:_layouts/post.html)
- Page layout: [_layouts/page.html](mdc:_layouts/page.html)

## Template Components
- Head section: [_includes/head.html](mdc:_includes/head.html)
- Header navigation: [_includes/header.html](mdc:_includes/header.html)
- Footer: [_includes/footer.html](mdc:_includes/footer.html)
- Cookie consent: [_includes/cookie-consent.html](mdc:_includes/cookie-consent.html)

## Styling Guidelines
- Use SCSS in [_sass/](mdc:_sass/) directory
- Compiled CSS goes to [css/](mdc:css/) directory
- Follow BEM methodology for CSS class naming
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure responsive design for mobile devices

## Jekyll Template Syntax
- Use Liquid templating language
- Variables: `{{ site.title }}`
- Conditionals: `{% if condition %}...{% endif %}`
- Loops: `{% for item in collection %}...{% endfor %}`
- Includes: `{% include filename.html %}`

## Asset Management
- Store static assets in [assets/](mdc:assets/) directory
- Use relative paths in templates
- Optimize images and other media files
- Include proper alt text for accessibility

## SEO and Meta Tags
- Use jekyll-seo-tag plugin for automatic meta tags
- Include proper title, description, and Open Graph tags
- Add structured data where appropriate
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy (H1, H2, H3)

## Performance Considerations
- Minimize HTTP requests
- Optimize images and assets
- Use efficient CSS selectors
- Consider lazy loading for images
- Implement proper caching headers
